In this article, President Trump discusses the importance of border security and the need for a physical barrier, or wall, along the US-Mexico border. He emphasizes the crisis of illegal immigration, drug trafficking, and human trafficking, and highlights the dangers and criminal activities that occur along the border. Trump also hears from individuals affected by the issues at the border, including the families of law enforcement officers who were killed by illegal immigrants. He commends the efforts of law enforcement, border patrol agents, and ICE officers, and expresses his support for their work. The article also mentions the need for legislative action to address immigration laws and provide resources for border security.